data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — with no workaround.**

EF Core 11 **fully removes** synchronous I/O for the Cosmos DB provider. In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async, but that opt-in no longer exists. Calling `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, or `SaveChanges()` against Cosmos now **always throws**.

**Fix — convert everything to async:**

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`. There is no opt-in or compatibility shim — async is the only path forward with the Cosmos DB provider in EF Core 11.

Tracking issue: https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
